      <h2><a name="info"></a>What is ERA?</h2>
      <h3>Education &amp; Research Archive</h3>

<p>ERA is the name for University of Alberta’s Digital Asset Management strategy as actively being developed and supported by the <a href="https://www.ualberta.ca">University of Alberta Libraries</a>. </p>

<p>ERA represents a coordinated approach to offering user-centred services in support of better access, discovery, shareability and preservation of digital research, teaching and learning objects. Scalability and extensibility are critical design requirements when dealing with wide ranging digital formats, including both raw and processed data. Security, stability, and trust are top of mind in providing the quality of service our users have come to depend on. For more on the technology behind ERA <a href="/about">see here</a>. </p>
      
